>1.3 Why might I want to use HPF?</A
></H1
>
<P
>HPF can provide a quick way of identifying not only HDF library compilation problems on many platforms but also potential performance issues of the library. 
HPF generates a daily warning report if there's a compilation error or a test instance takes longer than 20% or more. 
User can quickly locate the problem by looking at the daily graph. 
HPF also records the subversion revision number used in the library so the library developers can compare the source code differences that caused the performance degradation.</P
